      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GUS NZ (4) has delivered easily in his two starts at this circuit and distance since a spell, working in the middle stages in the first round of heats last week before finding the front and going on to score by 5.6m. Has has won four of six third-up attempts so should only be further improved. The one to beat. Last year's champion ARCEE PHOENIX (2) looks to be getting back to his best at the right time. Drew wider than this and worked when parked last week but stuck on well to place. Built through each round of last year's series and could do it again. GOTFEELINGSYOUKNOW (1) took advantage of this draw and used the sprint lane for a dead heat win last week. This race could pan out in a similar fashion so he can be competitive again. ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (10) shared the spoils with GOTFEELINGSYOUKNOW last week, her fourth win in seven tries here. Tricky draw this time but she has put together a string of wins and placings so respect. PARISIAN ARTISTE (3) draws well and may improve second up.",
